From 13cd034f2dbf32eb4195cf6f247c77ff0e230a45 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramya Gnanasekar <rgnanase@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 23 May 2025 19:57:32 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: CP: wifi: ath12k: Avoid beacon template for non-tx
 vif

Beacon template will be sent for transmitting vif and for non
transmitting vif beacon template will be sent with its transmitting vif
vdev. In case of MBSSID grouping for 6GHz, EMA paramater will not be sent from
hostapd and hence the existing code from upstream takes non ema path
where all the vifs are treated as transmitting and the beacon template
is sent for non transmitting vif causing Q6 assert.

Fix the issue by sending the transmitting vif vdev id in beacon template
for non transmitting vif.

Issue will be seen only when MBSSID grouping is enabled which is by
default enabled in QSDK.

Patch-dependency: MBSSID grouping FR

Signed-off-by: Ramya Gnanasekar <rgnanase@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -1818,6 +1818,11 @@ static int ath12k_mac_setup_bcn_tmpl(str
 			return ath12k_mac_setup_bcn_tmpl_ema(arvif, tx_arvif,
 							     link_conf->bssid_index);
 	} else {
+		/* Avoid setting beacon for non-tx vdevs if corresponding
+		 * tx vdev is unmapped.
+		 */
+		if (link_conf->nontransmitted)
+			return 0;
 		tx_arvif = arvif;
 	}
 
@@ -1863,7 +1868,7 @@ static int ath12k_mac_setup_bcn_tmpl(str
 		}
 	}
 
-	ret = ath12k_wmi_bcn_tmpl(arvif, &offs, bcn, NULL);
+	ret = ath12k_wmi_bcn_tmpl(tx_arvif, &offs, bcn, NULL);
 
 	if (ret)
 		ath12k_warn(ab, "failed to submit beacon template command: %d\n",
